    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation to the author's intent in its original canonical context. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from the sacred chambers through the priestly garment law to the perimeter measurement and its theological verdict. Ezekiel wrote in exile; the vision's architectural precision is a form of prophetic protest against the desecration that caused Israel's catastrophe, and a promise that God will rebuild what was profaned.",
